title: Nelson A. Rockefeller gubernatorial records, Office Subject Files, Third Administration, Series 37.3
finding_aid_title: A Guide to the Nelson A. Rockefeller gubernatorial records, Office Subject Files, Third Administration, Series 37.3
finding_aid_filing_title: Nelson A. Rockefeller gubernatorial records, Office Subject Files, Third Administration, Series 37.3

subnotes.content: This guide was compiled by Brendan Sobie, Rockefeller Archive Center, 1993 and 1994.

Major subjects contained in the files include:

Administration. Aging. Agriculture. Authorities and Commissions. Banking. Civil Defense. Commemorative Observance. Conservation. Consumers. Correction. Disasters. Discrimination. Education. Executive Clemency. Extradition. Fiscal. Fund raising. Government. Health & Sanitation. Honorary Designation. Horse Racing. Housing. Insurance. Investigations. Invitations. Judiciary. Labor. Law. Legislation. Licensing. Mental Hygiene. Military and Naval. Organizations. Parks and Recreation facilities. Personnel Administration. Politics. Property. Public Safety. Public Utilities. Public Works. Regrets. Resignations and Vacancies. Statements. Transportation. Veterans. Welfare. Youth.
Microfilm user copies are open for research. The archival material has been reformatted. Access to the original paper records is restricted.

Information regarding the Rockefeller Archive Center's preferred elements and forms of citation can be found at <extref href="http://www.rockarch.org/research/citations.php">http://www.rockarch.org/research/citations.php</extref>

Series 37 is arranged into 4 subseries:

Subseries 1: First Administration, 1959-1962. Subseries 2: Second Administration, 1963-1966. Subseries 3: Third Administration, 1967-1970. Subseries 4: Fourth Administration, 1971-1973.

Material is arranged alphabetically by subject within each subseries.
